OL,7,FResponding, Mr Lyons described a
OL,8,F"charade, dressed up as a debate on
OL,9,Fstandards in public life", adding he
OL,10,Frejected Ms McCullough's report.
OL,12,FHe also said he had, and has, "deep
OL,13,Fcompassion" for the families affected
OL,14,Fby the rioting.
OL,16,F"What they experienced was wrong. I
OL,17,Fhave always stood against violence and
OL,18,Fintimidation," he told MLAs.
